    <j.0:comment xml:lang="en">The Commission can accept certain amendments in principle: amendments 6 (each MS to make a declaration identifying its issuing and executing authorities); 9 partially (right to no self-incrimination should be able to be claimed under laws of either issuing or executing MS); 10 partially (formalities required by issuing authority to be followed in the executing MS to be subject to the safeguards in Art. 12); and 13 (but as a recital: the subsequent use of the acquired evidence does not prejudice rights of the defence in subsequent proceedings). (Amendment numbers follow the 6.4.04 provisional version of Resolution &amp;#13;
</j.0:comment>
